Name: sgRNA
Explanation: Original single guide-RNA scaffold.

Name: Flip + Extension (F+E) sgRNA
Explanation: Scaffold with A-U flip in position 4, and a duplex extension. Originally developed for CRISPR imaging.
Efficiency: CRISPR imaging signal-to-background ratio  improved by 5-fold.

Name: Optimized scaffold
Explanation: Scaffold was optimized by introducing a duplex extension and truncating the T-stretch to prevent premature transcription termination, replacing position 4 with a cytosine to disrupt the Pol III terminator signal.
Efficiency: Up to 10-fold increase in efficiency. Higher efficiency than (FE) sgRNA

Name: cr748
Explanation: Variant of the FE gRNA with higher activity.

Name: cr289
Explanation: Variant of the FE gRNA with higher activity.

Name: cr622
Explanation: Variant of the FE gRNA with higher activity.

Name: cr772
Explanation: Variant of the FE gRNA with higher activity.

Name: cr532
Explanation: Variant of the FE gRNA with higher activity.

Name: cr961
Explanation: Variant of the FE gRNA with higher activity.

Name: T-lock
Explanation: Scaffold with additional stable hairpin to prevent gRNA misfolding.
Efficiency: Cleavage efficiency increase of up to 2.5 fold in most extreme case for in vivo-transcribed sgRNAs.

Name: apegRNA-2
Explanation: Scaffold optimized for prime editing.

Name: RGen-6
Explanation: Scaffold with inceased activity for KO, base editing and prime editing. Designed by AI.
Efficiency: Increase of up to two-fold for KO efficiency, 2.5-fold for BE, and 1.2 fold for PE.

Name: Diversified pegRNA 318
Explanation: Scaffold optimized for prime editing. Also part of reduced sequence-homology set (entry 155-170).
Efficiency: Increase of up to five-fold for PE.

Name: Mutated proximal duplex
Explanation: Mutational analysis of scaffold. Similar efficiency as original scaffold in HEK293FT cells. Also known as RAR rescue-1 scaffold (10.1016/j.cell.2014.02.001). More self-editing than the original scaffold when used in combination with SpRY Cas9 (10.1186/s13059-020-02231-9).

Name: Truncated distal duplex

Name: Truncate linker

Name: Replace stem loop 2
Explanation: Mutational analysis of scaffold. Similar efficiency as original scaffold in HEK293FT cells. Also known as SL2 rescue scaffold (10.1016/j.cell.2014.02.001).

Name: Mutate stem loop 3

Name: GCCC-esgRNA
Explanation: Modified "Optimized sgRNA" with the replacement of  thymines at positions 2–5 with cytosines. Prevents self-editing in Cas9-NG-based base editors. Tested in rice (Oryza sativa)
